'''Kiskunság''' ({{lang-la|Cumania Minor}}<ref name="katolikus">{{cite news|url = http://lexikon.katolikus.hu/J/J%C3%A1szkun%20Ker%C3%BClet.html|title=Jászkun Kerület|publisher=Magyar Katolikus Lexikon |accessdate=}}</ref>) is a historical and geographical region in [[Hungary]] situated in the current [[{{Hungarian county name|Bács-Kiskun}}]] between [[Kalocsa]] and [[Szeged]]. Its territory is 2,423 km². Like other historical European regions called [[Cumania]], it is named for the [[Cumans]] ({{Lang-hu|Kunok}}), a historically very significant [[nomad]]ic tribe.

