'''Port Blair mean time''' was the [[time zone]] of the [[Andaman and Nicobar Islands]] of [[India]] in the [[Bay of Bengal]]. The time zone was set up during the early 19th century and remained in effect until January 1, 1906 when the [[Indian Standard Time]] became the official time of India.
